    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-29T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-29T21:00:00-05:00" n="579"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d579">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/11777: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-30T09:00:00+07:00"
                            >January 30, 1943—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>168. Department’s inquiry regarding antimony (No. 108, January 19 [<hi
                        rend="italic">20</hi>], 11 p.m). Russians are not obtaining the mineral for
                    transportation overland. Limited transport facilities preclude such an
                    operation.</p>
                <p>No information has reached Embassy indicating that the Japanese are acquiring the
                    mineral from unoccupied China. Chairman [of] Resources Commission states that
                    location of mines well within Free China facilitates control, that he has
                    received no reports of smuggling, and that he is convinced that, if Japanese are
                    obtaining antimony from Hunan, quantities are negligible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
